HEADWORD: organometallic
<hw>or`ga*no*me*tal"lic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or denoting, any one of a series
of compounds of certain metallic elements bound to organic radicals;
such as, methylmercury, zinc methyl, sodium ethyl, etc.; formerly
referred to as <altname>metalorganic</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

